Arafat Congratulates Israelis on Jewish New Year
JERUSALEM , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat has phoned Israeli leaders and prominent political figures to congratulate them on the Jewish New Year , Israel Radio reported Monday .
During the telephone conversation with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on Rosh Hashana , the two-day holiday beginning at sundown Sunday , Arafat wished him a happy new year , the radio said .
Sources in the Israeli Prime Minister 's Office said the two leaders also discussed the Israeli-Palestinian negotiations over the Israeli withdrawal from the West Bank and agreed to complete them through American mediation .
Arafat and Netanyahu have agreed during the visit of U.S. peace envoy Dennis Ross to the region earlier this month to hold direct talks .
The two will be in New York later this week to attend the General Assembly of the United Nations .
The Palestinian News Agency Wafa reported that Arafat also extended New Year greetings to Israeli President Ezer Weizman , Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai , Labor Party leader Ehud Barak , former Prime Minister Shimon Peres and Leah Rabin , widow of slain Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin .
To each of them , Arafat said in Hebrew " Shana Tova , " or " Happy New Year , " the agency reported .
